## To Gain the Prize

I sought to **acquire** a noble prize,  
A goal that shimmered, splendid and sublime,  
Beneath ambition's bright, demanding skies,  
Devoting heart and thought to conquer time.  

Yet shadows crept where hopeful light had shone,  
A **fearful** doubt within the spirit grew,  
That whispered all my earnest toil was gone,  
And promised joy might never prove quite true.  

The striving hand, the will that pushed so fast,  
Felt bonds of unseen anguish tightening,  
Found confidence in splintered shards at last,  
**Tearing** the dream from which my hope took wing.  
But wisdom blooms from what we've dearly paid,  
The richest gain is in the price displayed.  

